    • flagAsBool

      default boolean flagAsBool(@NotNull @NotNull List<String> kbStrings, Integer index, String key)
      Given the list of flags (string in the format "Key: boolean"), get the flag at the index and extract the value of the given key as a boolean.
      Parameters:
      kbStrings - The list of flag strings.
      index - The index of the list we want the flag string from.
      key - The substring to slice off. Example: "PVP: "
      Returns:
      True if the key was true, False if the key was false or not a boolean.
